CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 18, 1970, pg. 11, reads: "Digs 'Diz' - Attractive Darlene Washington, a junior at the University of Pittsburgh where she is education major, is a jazz buff and collects jazz albums as a hobby. One of her favorites is Dizzy Gillespie.  She was among the fans at the Adult Center of Allegheny Community College in Homewood-Brushton area when the internationally famous trumpet star performed there last week."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Darlene Washington wearing afro and dashiki, holding cigarette, and standing next to photographic display of African dancers and wildlife
